Sentencas: The electrochemical performance and microstructure stability of PrBaCo2O5+delta (PBCO) cathode are investigated in CO2-containing atmospheres for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Performance degradation of double-perovskite PrBaCo2O5+δ oxygen electrode in CO2 containing atmospheres

Sentencas: Electrochemical impedance spectra results confirm obvious performance degradation of the PBCO cathodes in the presence of CO2 impurity, especially in high CO2 concentration condition.
Titulo: Performance degradation of double-perovskite PrBaCo2O5+δ oxygen electrode in CO2 containing atmospheres

Sentencas: Microstructure and structural analyses reveal the formation of insulating BaCO3 nanoparticles at the PBCO surface, which is considered as the primary reason for the loss of electrode activity.
Titulo: Performance degradation of double-perovskite PrBaCo2O5+δ oxygen electrode in CO2 containing atmospheres

Sentencas: This study highlights the important role of surface segregated BaO species in determining the activity and long-time stability of PBCO electrode.
Titulo: Performance degradation of double-perovskite PrBaCo2O5+δ oxygen electrode in CO2 containing atmospheres
